answers.body_markdown:
The [`slice()`][1] method is only avalible on the Array type, and is not avalible on a plain object.

To achieve what you require, you could extract the key/value entries of your input object with [`Object#entries()`][2] and then [`Array#reduce()`][3] the reduce the first &quot;n&quot; number of entries to the reduced to the result.

In code that could be expressed as:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const obj = {
    &quot;key1&quot;: &quot;val1&quot;,
    &quot;key2&quot;: &quot;val2&quot;,
    &quot;key3&quot;: &quot;val3&quot;,
    &quot;key4&quot;: &quot;val4&quot;,
    &quot;key5&quot;: &quot;val5&quot;,
    &quot;key6&quot;: &quot;val6&quot;,
    &quot;key7&quot;: &quot;val7&quot;
    };

    const includeCount = 3;

    const res = Object.entries(obj).reduce((acc, [key, value], index) =&gt; 
      // Accumulate current entry [key/value] to result object (acc) if
      // index before includeCount, otherwise just return result object
      ((index &lt; includeCount) ? { ...acc, [key] : value } : acc), 
      {});

    console.log(res);

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/slice
  [2]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/entries
  [3]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/Reduce

You can `slice` the array you get from `Object.entries` and then build a new object with [`Object.fromEntries`][1] (but keep in mind that `Object.fromEntries` is only supported in ES2019):

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const data = {
      &quot;key1&quot;: &quot;val1&quot;,
      &quot;key2&quot;: &quot;val2&quot;,
      &quot;key3&quot;: &quot;val3&quot;,
      &quot;key4&quot;: &quot;val4&quot;,
      &quot;key5&quot;: &quot;val5&quot;,
      &quot;key6&quot;: &quot;val6&quot;,
    };

    const result = Object.fromEntries(Object.entries(data).slice(0, 3));
    console.log(result);

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


  [1]: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/fromEntries

